The paper is about evaluating different neural machine translation architectures, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the performance of these architectures in terms of their ability to model long-range dependencies and extract semantic features, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper uses convolutional networks, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV), to evaluate their performance in NLP tasks.
